<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="167" type="conservation">
<subSection pageId="6" pageNumber="167" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,338,580]" box="[136,218,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,218,338,364]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,218,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Threat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,338,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
1. Native habitat of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bor" authorityYear="1951" box="[381,583,374,400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Themeda" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxicola">
<emphasis box="[381,583,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Themeda saxicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is under a considerable anthropogenic pressure. The stone quarrying activities were observed in the habitat of this species; and this can become major cause for population reduction (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1392,410,437]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,207,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,190,1941]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. A. Mining activity in Raisili Hill. B. Invasive alien species in Themeda saxicola habitat." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5912630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5912630/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Fig. 5 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,338,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
2. The native habitat is invaded by alien invasive species such as: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Candolle 1836: 181) King &amp; Robinson (1970: 223)" authorityName="King &amp; Robinson" authorityPageNumber="223" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="181" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ageratina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ligustrina">
<emphasis box="[968,1198,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Ageratina ligustrina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[1215,1443,446,472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2116" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1836) Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis, vol. 5. Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 181 pp." type="book" year="1836">Candolle 1836: 181</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="King, R. M. &amp; Robinson, H." box="[136,483,482,508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" pagination="223" refId="ref2438" refString="King, R. M. &amp; Robinson, H. (1970) Studies in the Eupatorieae (Compositae). XIX. New combinations in Areratina. Phytologia 19: 223. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14771" type="journal article" year="1970">King &amp; Robinson (1970: 223)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schumacher 1827: 44) Morrone (2010: 129)" authorityName="Morrone" authorityPageNumber="129" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Schumacher" baseAuthorityPageNumber="44" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[496,1248,482,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cenchrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis box="[496,726,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Cenchrus purpureus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schumacher, H. C. F." box="[741,991,482,508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2643" refString="Schumacher, H. C. F. (1827) Beskrivelse af Guineeiske Planter som ere fundne af dankse Botanikere, isaer af Etatsraad Thonning ved F. C. Schumacher, Saerskilt aftrykt af det kongelige danske Videnskabers Selskabs Skrifter. Kjobenhavn, 44 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 51454" type="book" year="1827">Schumacher 1827: 44</bibRefCitation>
) Morrone (2010: 129)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 627)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="627" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camara">
<emphasis box="[1264,1452,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Lantana camara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[136,377,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2557" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum 2. Salvius, Stockholm, 627 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 627)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1759: 1100) Kuntze (1891: 525)" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityPageNumber="525" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="1100" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[430,1216,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Mesosphaerum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suaveolens">
<emphasis box="[430,731,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Mesosphaerum suaveolens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[745,984,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2538" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1759) Systema Naturae Editio decima, reformata. Stockholm, 1100 pp." type="book" year="1759">Linnaeus 1759: 1100</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuntze, C. E. O." box="[998,1216,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2486" refString="Kuntze, C. E. O. (1891) Revisio Generum Plantarum: vascularium omnium atque cellularium multarum secundum leges nomeclaturae internationales cum enumeratione plantarum exoticarum in itinere mundi collectarum. Leipzig, 525 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 124064" type="book" year="1891">Kuntze (1891: 525)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1231,1325,518,545]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1965,1987]" captionTargetBox="[196,1390,207,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[151,1436,190,1941]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. A. Mining activity in Raisili Hill. B. Invasive alien species in Themeda saxicola habitat." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5912630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5912630/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Fig. 5 B</figureCitation>
). There are possibilities that these alien species can spread all over these habitats and affect these populations.
</paragraph>
</subSection>
<subSection pageId="6" pageNumber="167" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,625,868]" box="[136,535,625,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,535,625,652]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,535,625,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">IUCN threat category assessment</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,625,868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
Area of occupancy (AOO) was calculated using GeoCat (
<bibRefCitation author="Bachman, S. &amp; Moat, J. &amp; Hill, A. W. &amp; de la Torre, J. &amp; Scott, B." box="[792,1039,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" pagination="117 - 126" refId="ref2001" refString="Bachman, S., Moat, J., Hill, A. W., de la Torre, J. and Scott, B. (2011) Supporting Red List threat assessments with GeoCAT: geospatial conservation assessment tool. In: Smith, V. &amp; Penev, L. (Eds.) e-Infrastructures for data publishing in biodiversity science. ZooKeys 150: 117 - 126. (Version BETA) *" type="journal article" year="2011">
Bachman 
<emphasis box="[909,966,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
) online software developed by Kew Botanic Gardens. GPS locations of two localities of occurrence were used as input data and grid size was kept 
<quantity box="[1379,1436,698,724]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1436,1444,698,712]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
. Based on GPS data of the populations in the two localities, we found AOO to be 
<quantity box="[1045,1102,734,760]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1102,1110,734,748]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
and EOO to be 
<quantity box="[1292,1364,734,760]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="42.0">42 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1363,1371,734,748]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
(i.e. in Deomali area is 
<quantity box="[317,388,770,796]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="42.0">42 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[387,395,770,784]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
and in Raisili 
<quantity box="[557,613,770,796]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="6.0">6 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[613,621,770,784]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
). We have also observed shrinkage in the habitats due to mining activities. The EOO is &lt;
<quantity box="[289,373,806,832]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[373,381,806,820]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
and AOO is &lt;
<quantity box="[538,608,806,832]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[607,615,806,820]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2</superScript>
. Thus, based on 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[800,949,806,832]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" refId="ref2312" refString="IUCN (2022) The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2021 - 3. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge U. K. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org (assessed 8 January 2022)" type="url" year="2022">IUCN (2022)</bibRefCitation>
we assign this plant as Critically Endangered (CR) under B1 B2biii.
</paragraph>
</subSection>
<subSection pageId="6" pageNumber="167" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,913,1120]" box="[136,414,913,940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,414,913,940]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,414,913,940]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Conservation measures</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,913,1120]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">
The population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bor" authorityYear="1951" box="[340,541,950,976]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Themeda" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxicola">
<emphasis box="[340,541,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">Themeda saxicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Raisili hill is good and healthy. But it will be in threat if this hill is not protected from mining activity. Whereas the population of Deomali is less, with no mining activity reported. But its population growth is affected by the encroachment of alien invasive species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,913,1120]" box="[189,970,1058,1084]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">1. Mining activities should be controlled and if possible, minimized.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,913,1120]" box="[189,1308,1094,1120]" pageId="6" pageNumber="167">2. Implementation of species recovery programme to protect the populations in the native habitats.</paragraph>
</subSection>
